WINE, unlike fruit juice or even bourbon, is not a fixed, repetitive experience — but changes its personality and taste qualities as it develops and matures in the bottle. Because of this, the wine-lover is prone to be a bit fickle and does not insist on drinking the same wine from day to day, no matter how good — he chooses to adventure among the

world’s vineyards for new, interesting taste experiences.
